  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 5th level in warlock, you can attack with your Pact Weapon twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.</p><p>Additionally, whenever you expend a warlock Pact Magic Slot, your Pact Weapon consumes a portion of the magical power. You gain an amount of consumed power equal to the level of the Pact Magic Slot expended, and you cannot have more consumed power than your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1) at any given time. Once per turn, when you take the Attack action with your Pact Weapon you can expend one consumed power to make an additional attack.</p><p>The power consumed by your Pact Weapon lasts until you complete a long rest, after which it is lost.</p>",
